      "info": {
        "description": "The OPEN counterpart to sir-epidemic: identical compartment topology (S->I->R with non-draining I-Sensor control), but Recovered drains to an external Mortality sink across the system boundary. Because mass crosses the boundary, the model is NOT closed: internal mass (compartment storage + internal in-flight) is no longer invariant, but obeys the exact open-system balance internal(t) = internal(0) - cumulative deaths. Contrast with sir-epidemic.json (closed, total mass conserved to machine epsilon). Demonstrates BERT reasoning about open vs. closed systems. Synchronous update mode; seed storages via initial_state (S=100, I=5, R=0).",
        "id": "S0",
        "level": 0,
        "name": "Open SIR Epidemic"
